    <item>
      <title>BareStage Presents: "Wonder Girl", Nov 15-24</title>
      <link>http://events.berkeley.edu/index.php/calendar/sn/pubaff.html?event_ID=70618&amp;date=2013-11-17</link>
      <description>Everyone wants to be a hero because no one can imagine a hero losing. From the mind of award-winning playwright and Cal student Weston Scott,Wonder Girl tells the story of a teenage girl that gains super powers, along with the responsibility that shapes it. As she decidedly tries to make the world into a better place, she faces incompetent super heroes, pun-loving masterminds, and apathetic townspeople who all have differing visions of an ideal community. An impactful and engaging score by local musician Stefano Flavoni illuminates the world of comic books from the initial triumphant notes to the final, longing refrain. By questioning the true meaning of a hero, Wonder Girl examines a world in which the protagonist canâ€™t win, but wants nothing else. Combining humor, action, music, and the tragic, this musical is a true whirlwind force that drives toward an exhilarating ending. Wonder Girl-Someone Better Shake Things Up.&lt;br /&gt;&#13;
Shows are at 8pm friday and Saturday &amp; 5pm on Sunday</description>
      <guid>http://events.berkeley.edu/index.php/calendar/sn/pubaff.html?event_ID=70618&amp;date=2013-11-17</guid>
